quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  26,20,"He said, "I did that at that time when I was one of the unaware people."
  26,21,"Then I fled from you when I feared you. Thereafter my Lord granted wisdom to me and made me among the messengers."
  26,22,"And this is the favor with which you are obliging me - that you have enslaved the children of Isra il.""
  26,23,"The Pharaoh said, "And what is the Lord of the worlds?""
  26,24,"He (Musa) said, "Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever there is between them, if you are to believe""
  26,25,"He (the Pharaoh) said to those around him, "Are you not hearing?""
  26,26,"He (Musa) said, "Your Lord and the Lord of your early forefathers""
  26,27,"He (the Pharaoh) said, "Your messenger who is sent to you is a mad man indeed.""
  26,28,"He (Musa) said, "Lord of the East and the West and whatever there is between them, if you are to understand""
  26,29,"He (the Pharaoh) said, "If you take to a God other than me, I will certainly put you among those imprisoned.""
  26,30,"He (Musa) said "Will you (do this) even if I bring to you something evident?""
  26,31,"He said, "Then bring it, if you are one of the truthful.""
  26,32,"So, he threw down his staff, and in no time it was a serpent, clearly visible,"
  26,33,"and he drew out his hand, and right then it was a white light to the onlookers."
  26,34,"He (the Pharaoh) said to the chiefs around him "This man is certainly an expert sorcerer"."
  26,35,"He wants to expel you from your land with his sorcery. So what do you suggest?""
  26,36,"They said, "Leave him and his brother alone for a while and send to the cities men to collect,"
  26,37,"so that they bring to you every highly expert sorcerer.""
  26,38,"So the sorcerers were assembled for the appointed time of a known day,"
  26,39,"and it was said to the people, "Would you assemble,"